  "articles": [
    {
      "id": "poem-moshang-001",
      "title": "陌上潇潇",
      "category": "文学诗歌",
      "date": "2025-06-01",
      "readTime": 3,
      "excerpt": "采梌几尝风雨意，孤身一往天涯人。",
      "image": "",
      "content": "<div style=\"max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;\"><div style=\"margin-bottom:3.5rem;\"><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.05rem;font-style:italic;color:#9e9284;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin-bottom:2.4rem;\">— 吕庭锐</p><div style=\"display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.15rem 3rem;margin-bottom:3rem;\"><div style=\"border-left:2px solid rgba(124,77,184,0.15);padding-left:1.4rem;\"><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">陌上潇潇杜宇去，</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">月下悄悄夏虫吟。</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">采梌几尝风雨意，</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">孤身一往天涯人。</p></div><div style=\"border-left:2px solid rgba(124,77,184,0.15);padding-left:1.4rem;\"><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">云深路遥憯不明，</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">枯草落花朽柴门。</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">残漏不解天地阔，</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.55rem;line-height:2.6;letter-spacing:0.2em;color:#18160f;margin:0;\">几声将断几声深。</p></div></div></div><hr style=\"border:none;border-top:1px solid rgba(24,22,15,0.08);margin:2.8rem 0;\"/><div><p style=\"font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.64rem;font-weight:500;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#7c4db8;margin-bottom:1.8rem;\">English rendering</p><div style=\"display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.15rem 3rem;margin-bottom:2rem;\"><div style=\"border-left:2px solid rgba(124,77,184,0.12);padding-left:1.4rem;\"><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">The cuckoo leaves the path, wind in its cry,</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">Beneath the moon, summer insects hum reply.</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">I have tasted what wind and rain intend,</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">Alone, I walk toward the world's far end.</p></div><div style=\"border-left:2px solid rgba(124,77,184,0.12);padding-left:1.4rem;\"><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">Clouds thicken, roads stretch — grief has no name,</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">Withered grass, fallen flowers, a rotting gate frame.</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">The failing clepsydra knows not sky's vast breadth —</p><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:1.08rem;line-height:2.1;font-style:italic;color:#3a3428;margin:0;\">A few notes nearly gone, a few more sinking to their depth.</p></div></div><p style=\"font-family:'EB Garamond',serif;font-size:0.9rem;font-style:italic;color:#9e9284;margin-top:2rem;line-height:1.9;border-top:1px solid rgba(24,22,15,0.06);padding-top:1.6rem;\"><em>Notes —</em> 杜宇: the cuckoo, in classical verse a bird of longing and farewell, its cry said to carry the ache of those who cannot return. 残漏: a clepsydra, the ancient water-clock that measures time drop by drop; here it runs nearly dry, yet remains oblivious to the immensity of heaven and earth it has outlasted.</p></div></div>"
    },
